"title": "7359: Feast of Trumpets",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7359",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>This feast, which is not specifically mentioned as such in the OT, took place at the observance of the new moon in the month of Tishri (September/October). It signalled the end of the agricultural year.</p>\n<h2>It was to be a day of rest, commemorated with the sounding of trumpets</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:24-Lev23:25\">LEV 23:24–23:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:1\">NUM 29:1</a></p>\n<h2>Offerings were made to God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:25\">LEV 23:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:2-Num29:5\">NUM 29:2–29:5</a></p>\n<h2>Celebrated after the exile</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:2-Neh8:6\">NEH 8:2–8:6</a></p>",
